Article 12: Lawmaking

Section 1:
A proposal for a law may be submitted when the proposing Voluntary Adherent holds at least [Proposal Threshold: _% of DAO tokens].

Section 2:
A proposal becomes a Bill when it receives approval from at least [Approval Threshold: _% of DAO token secondments].

Section 3:
A Bill becomes law by a majority vote with a sufficient quorum [what percentage is sufficient?].

Section 4:
Once adopted, such laws shall be binding upon all Voluntary Adherents, provided they are consistent with this Constitution.
Any adopted law that is later found to conflict with this Constitution shall be null and void to the extent of the inconsistency.
